    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix race condition in nr_generate_prs function\n\n### Summary\nThe `nr_generate_prs` function in `openair1/PHY/NR_TRANSPORT/nr_prs.c` was experiencing race conditions due to unsafe memory accesses when timer expiry handlers and normal message processing both accessed the txdataF buffer concurrently.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/NR_TRANSPORT/nr_prs.c`: Added bounds checking to prevent out-of-bounds writes to the txdataF buffer\n- Added proper index validation before accessing txdataF array elements\n- Updated debug logging to use validated indices\n- Added bounds checking for final debug output\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder heavy load conditions with concurrent timer events and PRS generation, the system would occasionally crash with segmentation faults or produce incorrect PRS patterns. Memory corruption was observed in adjacent data structures when running with memory debugging tools.\n\nTo reproduce:\n1. Configure multiple PRS resources with overlapping time slots\n2. Trigger high-frequency timer events that access the txdataF buffer\n3. Run PRS generation concurrently with timer handlers\n4. Monitor for memory corruption or segmentation faults\n\nThe issue manifests as intermittent crashes during PRS generation under concurrent access scenarios.\n"
}